## Postman Collection
The following Postman collections are available:
- `Microservices-API-Collection.postman_collection.json` - Complete microservices testing
- `Student-Management-API.postman_collection.json` - Student service testing
- `Fee-Collection-API.postman_collection.json` - Fee service testing

## Instructions for Adding Screenshots
1. Run the microservices using `docker-compose up`
2. Test each endpoint using Postman
3. Take screenshots of:
   - Request and response for each endpoint
   - Database query results
   - Docker service status
   - Any error scenarios
4. Insert screenshots in the appropriate sections above

## Testing Checklist
- [ ] All CRUD operations tested via gateway
- [ ] Direct service endpoints tested
- [ ] Database entries verified
- [ ] Error handling scenarios tested
- [ ] Service health checks verified
- [ ] Docker services status confirmed
- [ ] Postman collection imported and tested

## Notes
- Ensure all services are running before testing
- Use the provided Postman collections for consistent testing
- Database connections can be verified using MySQL Workbench or similar tools
- Gateway port 8080 should be used for all client-facing operations
